{[#] This is the trademark Ragozin-pawn structure. It usually arises after the
exchange of bishop for knight on c3. It is a dynamic pawn structure, meaning
that it can transpose into several other pawn structures (#2, #3, #6, for
example). For Black, it is often important to get his pawn to c5 before White
pushes his backward c-pawn. He is ready to even sacrifice the c-pawn in some
cases, obtaining counterplay against White's disconnected queenside pawns (a2,
c3, c5).}  *

