{[#] This pawn structure is very similar to #3, but the position of the pawn
on b2 rather than c3 makes a big difference. While Black still usually wants
to use his pawn majority on the queenside, White has two undermining plans: 1)
b2-b3 and 2) e3-e4. In both cases, he would like to reduce the potential of
Black's queenside pawn mass.}  *

