20. Rac1 Re8 21. Ne4 Qd7 22. Qb3 Bf8 23. h3 Re6 24. Nc5 Rxe1+ 25. Rxe1 Bxc5 26.
dxc5 $11 {1-0 (42) Lopez Martinez,J (2552)-Peralta,F (2574) Lorca 2016}) 20...
b6 21. Ne4 Qd7 22. Qg3 f6 23. Bf4 Nxf4 24. Qxf4 Qxd4 25. Qc7 Rae8 26. Qxc6 Qxb2
$17 {1-0 Ragger,M (2694)-Inarkiev,E (2714)/32nd ECC Open 2016 (61)}) (11. Qb5 {
was a concrete move that confused Black in the game Nechaeva,M (2424)
-Kashlinskaya,A (2452) St Petersburg RUS 2017, ½-½ (41) , but Black should
be doing just fine with} c5 $5 $146 12. dxc5 Qa5 13. Qxa5 Bxa5 14. Bxf6 Nxf6
15. Rc1 Ne4 16. Ke2 Bxc3 17. bxc3 Rfc8 18. c4 Rxc5 19. cxd5 Rxd5 $11) ({
Similarly,} 11. a3 {can be met with} Bxc3+ 12. bxc3 c5 $11) 11... c6 12. a3 ({
In case of} 12. Ne5 {Black can simply retreat} Be7 ({or even play} 12... Qe8 {
transposing into the variation above.}) 13. Nxd7 Nxd7 14. Bxe7 Qxe7 15. a3 a5
$11 {1/2-1/2 (30) Batchimeg,T (2391)-Munkhgal,G (2446) Ulaanbaatar 2016}) 12...
Bd6 {[#] I prefer this move to 12...Be7 because the bishop is more active on
