1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 a6 {[#]} {Some players prefer quiet
development with} 5. e3 {shifting the focus from the opening to the middlegame.
Black has many good options, such as transposing into Tarrasch defense with 5..
.c5, or into the Queen's gambit accepted with 5...dxc4. While being sufficient
to equalize, these variations usually lead to simplifications in the center.} (
