was unpleasantly surprised when he quickly answered:} h6 {previously, 8...Bd6
and 8...c6 have been played.} 9. Bf4 {and now} Bf5 $1 {I was kicking myself
for not checking this simple move in my preparation. Black improves his bishop
to the ideal square.} ({It should be noted that Black also has a Ragozin-like
alternative here:} 9... Bb4 $5 10. Bd3 (10. a3 Bxc3+ 11. bxc3 c5 12. Bd3 O-O
13. O-O c4 {with a good version of pawn structure #3.} 14. Bc2 Ne4 15. Bxe4
dxe4 16. Nd2 Bd5 17. a4 b6 $11) 10... c5 11. dxc5 Nxc5 12. O-O Bxc3 13. bxc3
O-O $11 {and Black was fine in the pawn structure #2, in the game Volkov, S 
